The paper deals with privacy-preserving techniques for analyzing social network graphs, which involves techniques from data structures (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses potential privacy threats and attacks (cs.CR). The focus on social network analysis and graph clustering suggests that cs.SI (social and information networks) is also a likely category.
